    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's not just a \"symptom.\" it's the reality. i built my entire identity around being a person who discovered something meaningful. now that the truth is out, that person doesn't exist. there's no \"value\" in a shell that's just pretending to be something it's not. i feel like i'm just performing a role in a life that doesn't even belong to me anymore. it feels so heavy, like there's no point in even trying to fix it.",
